						<div class="postbody">(and in case it isn't painfully obvious, I am that AH.)
<br />
<br />Addendum: during this discussion, I misunderstood the specific concept of "rectangular" w.r.t. Solar Wars -- that the values are components of the vector.
<br />
<br />There are a few things that, in practical use, we use rectangular coordinates for.  Identity of location, for one.  (Hell, we abstract the spherical coordinates to rectangular ones every time we look at a cylindrical map projection.)  But (now that I really think about it) we actually use polar abstractions a lot more than HS/college math lets on.  I may say that I'm going 3 feet north and 4 yards west of where I am, but I don't travel that way; I turn straight toward there and walk 5 feet.  (Again, spherical -&gt; rectangular abstraction, but you get my point.)</div>

